        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> There is currently no such thing as a \"map option\", so the first step is to define such a thing. However, what should happen if a \"map option\" gets extended so that it is no longer a \"map option\"?\r\n\r\nI thought there was, as they exist on the lua API: https://neovim.io/doc/user/lua.html#vim.opt:get()\r\n```help\r\n    For values that are comma-separated maps, a table will be returned with\r\n    the names as keys and the values as entries: >\r\n        vim.cmd [[set listchars=space:_,tab:>~]]\r\n\r\n        print(vim.inspect(vim.opt.listchars:get()))\r\n        --  { space = \"_\", tab = \">~\", }\r\n\r\n        for char, representation in pairs(vim.opt.listchars:get()) do\r\n            print(char, \"->\", representation)\r\n        end\r\n\r\n```",
            "created_at": "2022-07-30T07:28:31Z",
